The discussion centered on the role of development agencies in recognizing climate change benefits as "co-benefits" in relation to core development benefits. It highlighted how Multilateral Development Banks (MDBs) can credit financing adaptation without valuing avoided losses. The conversation addressed the challenges in understanding risk reduction contributions and the need for better metrics in building climate resilience. It also covered the scope for private investment in adaptation based on the maturity and credit rating of recipient countries. The analysis included insights from a bar chart depicting the share of quantified dividends across various sub-sectors, emphasizing Energy's high percentage for Dividend 3 and the mixed contributions of dividends in Forestry/Nature, Transport, and Water Resources.
